# Windows Firewall Rules Configuration
# Format: RULE_NAME|DIRECTION|ACTION|PROTOCOL|PORT|HOSTNAME|COMMENT
#
# RULE_NAME:  Unique name for the firewall rule (no spaces recommended)
# DIRECTION:  Inbound or Outbound
# ACTION:     Allow or Block
# PROTOCOL:   TCP, UDP, or Any (leave empty for any)
# PORT:       Port number (leave empty for any port)
# HOSTNAME:   Dynamic DNS hostname to resolve
# COMMENT:    Description of the rule (optional)
#
# Examples:

# Allow SSH from NAS
# AllowSSHFromNAS|Inbound|Allow|TCP|22|nas.example.com|SSH access from NAS

# Allow RDP from office
# AllowRDPFromOffice|Inbound|Allow|TCP|3389|office.example.com|RDP access from office

# Allow HTTPS from backup server
# AllowHTTPSFromBackup|Inbound|Allow|TCP|443|backup.example.com|HTTPS from backup server

# Allow SMB from NAS
# AllowSMBFromNAS|Inbound|Allow|TCP|445|nas.example.com|SMB file sharing from NAS

# Allow all traffic from trusted host
# AllowAllFromTrusted|Inbound|Allow||||trusted.example.com|Allow all from trusted host

# Block outbound to specific host
# BlockOutboundToHost|Outbound|Block|||blocked.example.com|Block traffic to specific host
